            "description": "Method: POST\nURL: {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users\nAuth: Required via Authorization header\nHeaders: Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}, Content-Type: application/json\nQuery: None\nBody: JSON from create-user UI: img, full_name, phone, nationality, shirt_type, shirt_number, work_schedule, password, status\nResponse: message only, Worker created successfully.\nNotes: Admin only. username defaults to phone. password defaults to phone if omitted. nationality_name defaults to nationality and nationality_code defaults to UNKNOWN when omitted. shirt_number is used as worker_code internally. Use GET /api/admin/users with search or GET /api/admin/users/{id} when the frontend needs worker details."
